1 a public school a program for a school garden which meets the
2 requirements set forth in subsection 3.
3 3. For a nonprofit organization to receive an allocation of
4 money to provide a program for a school garden pursuant to
5 subsection 2, the program must:
6 (a) Create and maintain a school garden at the school.
7 (b) Have a curriculum that:
8 (1) Includes a comprehensive science, technology,
9 engineering and mathematics school garden program. Such a
10 program must include, without limitation, a science, technology,
11 engineering and mathematics curriculum for outdoor or hydroponic
12 gardens for pupils in kindergarten through grade 12 that is tailored
13 to pupils of the appropriate grade levels at the school;
14 (2) Is written specifically for Nevada and the desert
15 environment of Nevada;
16 (3) Complies with the standards of content and performance
17 for a course of study in science adopted by the State Board of
18 Education pursuant to NRS 389.520;
19 (4) Uses experiential learning or project-based learning to
20 teach science, technology, engineering, arts and mathematics;
21 (5) Is designed with the assistance of teachers and other
22 educational personnel with experience at the appropriate grade
23 levels at the school; and
24 (6) Involves supervised learning experiences for the pupils at
25 the school in a classroom and a school garden.
26 (c) Provide the school with assistance from members of the
27 community, including, without limitation, trained educators, local
28 farmers and local chefs.
29 (d) Provide pupils with the:
30 (1) Ability to operate a farmer’s market to sell the produce
31 from the school garden; and
32 (2) Opportunity to have a local chef or employee of a school
33 who works in food services demonstrate how to cook a meal using
34 the produce grown from the school garden.
35 (e) Establish garden teams comprised of teachers and, if such
36 persons are available, parents and members of the community. Each
37 garden team shall meet at least once each month.
38 (f) Require any local nonprofit or community-based
39 organization which will provide services to implement the program
40 for a school garden to have at least 2 years of experience
41 implementing such a program.
42 4. Money allocated pursuant to subsection 2 may be used to:
43 (a) Provide professional development for teachers regarding the:
44 (1) Use of a school garden to teach pupils with disabilities,
45 including, without limitation, training for teaching such pupils
